Quote: [Quoting Hursthouse] Here and there [in the wild mountain region of south-west Nelson], in some secluded nook, a few miserable natives, the remnants of early fugitives from the massacres on the eastern side, true `children of the mist' and `wild men of the woods,' have raised their little huts to snare the `kiwi' and the `weka,' unmolested and unseen.
